markdown: MEXICO'72 X congreso internacional de nutrición <::A stylized drawing of a figure, possibly a deity, in an ancient Mesoamerican art style. The figure is depicted in profile, facing left, with a large, elaborate headdress that has three distinct elements on top. It has a prominent nose, a fanged mouth, and circular ear ornaments. The figure is holding a large corn cob in its left hand. Its body is geometric, with a trapezoidal torso and skirt-like lower body. In its right hand, it holds a basket-like object filled with what appears to be corn or other plant elements. The background has a textured, vertical striped pattern.: figure::>
